data.value:
Is this truly a DNA pirating software? Yes and No. With this, you can artificially reconstruct a subject's DNA. This makes it a pirate. However, it does has its limits. Since it is purely based on matches, it can only reveal if you have access to the DNA of the subject's close matches. Hence, there is absolutely no risk of privacy or piracy in using the software. I named it Pirate DNA just for fun.
Why did you built this? Is it for the purpose of pirating DNA through matches? No. not at all. I designed this to create artificial ancestor profiles through matches.
